entries.content:
Perfect! I can see that the CSS custom properties for focus states have already been added to the `:root` selector (lines 90-94 in index.html):

```css
/* Focus States */
--focus-ring-color: var(--color-teal-500);
--focus-ring-width: 2px;
--focus-ring-offset: 2px;
--focus-ring-style: solid;
```

These variables meet all the acceptance criteria:
- ✅ `--focus-ring-color` uses teal-500 (accessible, high-contrast color)
- ✅ `--focus-ring-width` set to 2px for consistent ring thickness
- ✅ `--focus-ring-offset` set to 2px for spacing between element and ring
- ✅ Variables complement the existing design system colors (using teal-500)

I can also see they're already being used in the focus styles for anchor tags (lines 186-189) and accent links (lines 199-202).

